\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Where would she sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh with us children. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes - she was - rather reserved. Rather re - people used to say - they supposed she was a lady. People used to say that. She was a lady.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. Yes. She loved children. She loved children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. And other people did too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Into the shop yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did she help in the shop a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No, not very much. No. Only just when she was wanted perhaps. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Would he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 If you had worries could you share them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well - we had to behave as we should you know what I mean towards them. As children should.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. We had to respect one another, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No. No. No. Not hit back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well now - grow up to be - good, I suppose and unselfish and kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Chapel. Yes. We all went to chapel we used to fill two rows. Even the Baby was ta
ken in long clothes. Yes, oh yes. Lovely times in the chapel. Lovely times we had years ago. Band of hope. Christian Endeavour. My father had a very big Band of Hope. Yes. Very big Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh no, they didn't like that. No. No. We never did, none of us, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh dear No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well we'd have a - a talking to. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well yes, you might be punished, you might have to - go to bed perhaps or do without something you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Who would punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 My father. Mm. A look was enough really at the table. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Do you ever remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No. I don't re - I don't remember, no. No, I don't remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Would your mother ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No, my mother wouldn't. No. She'd talk like but she wouldn't - hit us, she wouldn't punish us in that way, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Would she send you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, she would. Oh yes. She'd send us to bed. Yes. That's a punishment we used to get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Would you say you received the ideas that you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more importan
t part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No I don't think so, both of them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Not very much - in those days, no, not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, we'd get presents, yes, we didn't have the parties you know like they do today. We had a friend or two you see perhaps. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. You'd have - something special. Yes - well - something different from the ordinary day you know . . .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 And you'd have one or two guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Little friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Friends, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 With my mother and father on Christmas Day? Well - w
e used to - used to go to chapel of course on - Christmas morning and - had our Christmas dinner and - nothing - very - extra, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Organ. My organ, I had that when I was twelve. Yes. And a violin. Rowland. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 You played the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 My father. Yes. Yes. And my mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 And your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Not brothers. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Just Rowland played the violin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
My father. He was in a choir at Mount Pleasant - chapel in Pontypool when the chap - oh the old chapel that is the Tranch. He was a boy then at The Tranch. You see where he was born and in the choir there. And then th
ey build that new one - in Pontypool and my father was still in the choir there until a couple of years before he died. He had a beautiful bass - voice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Oh yes. On a Sunday Night always. The organ and - violin, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 And sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Oh yes, we played games, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, used to have books from Sunday school you see. And used to have prizes every year - from Sunday school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Any other books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, I think my father had books, yes Oh yes, he had a bookcase, I can remember. Bookcase on the - on the wall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Not very many newspapers no. My father
 wouldn't have - and he wouldn't have Sunday papers in the house. He wouldn't have them. He used to say they were not fit for - young people to read. In those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 I don't think so. Oh we used to have the Sunday Companion. I remember that. The Sunday Companion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What do you mean reading to us?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No, reading themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. Yes. My father used to love reading - the Sunday Companion.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 How about your mother, did she read at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Mother didn't read a great lot, no, no, my mother didn't read a great lot. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did they every read aloud to you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, sometimes they did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did they read aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Do you remember a funeral in you family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
Funeral? Oh well of course I can, can remember by sister's when she died you see. And she was only twenty-three. And - Leslie, I can remember Leslie of course. He was twenty - what was he, nineteen, yes, Leslie was
 nineteen. He was ill-five days with pneumonia. Only five days and then he was gone. Then I can remember my brother Reginald of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about Gertie's funeral
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What Gwladys who died when she was twelve, can you remember her dying and being buried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
Yes. I can remember - and my brother Rowland, of course. They were not what you call put in trousers-suits years ago until they were about three or four boys. They used to wear little dresses. I can remember when my sister Gwladys wa
s buried, and my brother Rowland, he had a little silk dress on with a black sash, and a little black hat. I can - I can see him - with that on, yes. That was for Gwladys' funeral, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about you, how were you dressed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Me, Oh black. Yes. Yes I had black and My mother had black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 And veils, we had a veil. And - oh yes, we had - had a veil, oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Who attended the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh dear. People from the chapel of course and neighbours and - oh yes, funerals in thos
e - those days were always well attended, those days you see. And they used to sing on the way until they got to the church. I remember when my father was buried it was a very big funeral. Very big funeral. He was a businessman you see, yes. And my mother
. And my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about your sister, would you go to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
Yes. We'd go. And Gwladys funeral. No. I don't think, no - I went I remember. I don't know - I don't know what about the others, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 You went though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 I did, yes, yes. And Rowland. And Rowland, yes. But he wasn't - he hadn't been britched as you call it, you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 He had a frock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, a frock with a black - black sash. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Was he taken to the funeral like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Do you remember what it was like, can you remember the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Not very much I can't really, it's a good many years ago isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about your other sister? She died when she was 23. Yes Gertie. Can you remember her funeral?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Oh yes. She had rather a big funeral too because - she belonged to the Sunday School and the Band of Hope you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What was that like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well there was just the same - like a funeral normally, you have - you have - everything black and they w
ore - they wore white gloves you see then. White gloves for - for a young person, yes, all the bearers had white gloves. For a young person. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Who would attend her funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 The neighbours and - people from the chapel you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Would you wear mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh I would, yes, my mother and I. Oh yes, my mother and I, we had our veils. Black veils. Well about - six months, perhaps more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes. And I remember it was cotton and the hobble skirts were worn then,
 I had a hobble skirt. Yes. I remember the hobble skirt, how tight it was you know. We had them made. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you wear black then for about six months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. In those days they did you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were you taken visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 When you were a child.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
Well we didn't - visit neighbours a lot, 'cos we never - ran in and out of people's houses, you know, we never did that. But we used - oh yes, we used to visit - friends . . . Belonged to chapel perhaps you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 With whom would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well - with my mother, of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were you taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 To the Drapery. Drapery. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 With whom would you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes sometimes, yes. Chapel perhaps you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Do you remember any outings with you parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. We used to go to Newport - half day in - to Bellvue Park on a Thursday, half-day, closing, yes, Bellevue Park on a Thursday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Would you go every Thursday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Not ever Thursday, no, not every Thursday. We used to hire the - governess cart and a pony you know and father used to drive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 That was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 How often would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well perhaps - every other week or - yes, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
The shop of course would be closed Bank Holidays. But oh we used to go - oh we used to have a picnic for - from the chapel perhaps you know - on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899892\charrsid810411 Easter time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
 we used to go - 'cos Easter in those days was warm. We used to put on our white dresses and white shoes. Oh it used to be lovely. And we used to go - from the school we used to go to a place called the Pond. It's - in Pontypool. Above Ponty
pool park. And we used to go up there for a picnic and put swings in the trees for us. And we used to have our picnic up there. And at Whitsun as well you know. Although Whitsun -time they used to hold - sports in the park - at Whitsun, and my father alwa
y
s took us on the Monday, and the Tuesday perhaps 'cos the horse - horses would be - running on the place. He used to like to see the horses you know. Oh yes, I can remember Blowdin. Yes and walking the tight rope. Yes. And my brother Rowland when he was s
mall and he was lost. We couldn't find him anywhere. So on our way home now we were going up the hill - up a hill and there was a - a crowd of people you know and we looked you know and there he was in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899892\charrsid810411 centre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411  and they were saying }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3880494\charrsid810411 \lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 oh its young Clarke it's Rowlie Clarke.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3880494\charrsid810411 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
 Oh yes, we used to have some lovely times on the holidays you know, yes. Yes. And then we'd have outings from the chapel you know we might go to Newport lighthouse yes to Newport Lighthouse and we went in the And then he learned to walk,
 that's lovely. He was a very - lovely baby. Lovely baby he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Of course you were that much older than him weren't you? You spoilt him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes we did. And my mother used to take him into town, into Pontypool you know in his pram. And we'd go
 into Howlett's the drapers, you know, perhaps she'd want something you know. Take the pram in you know. All the lady assistants used to all come around him. And take him out of the pram. They used to love him. Such a lovely baby he was. Yes. He was too.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about August Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
August. Now what about August Bank Holiday? What did we used to do with August Bank Holiday? May have something on at the chapel you know, a tea party or something like that you see. And sports. Yes, and sports.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No. No. No holiday. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about Saturdays in those days, when you were still at school, how did you spend Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 I used to do little odd jobs you know. And - perhaps I'd go out with my frie
nds perhaps. But we were not allowed to play on the road. Never. Never allowed to play in the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well Sunday of course we were usually in chapel all day, morning, afternoon and evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you have different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Oh yes, always. Best clothes. And you had to take care of them too. You did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 You said you put the hats away in a box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. I know because we were very careful. Well you had to be those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What kind of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 On Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No. No, nothing like that on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes, very wrong. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 My father was a Deacon in Congregational.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 He was Congregational?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes. English Congregational.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 How often would they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well they went - my father would go three times, but my mother - only in the evenings because of 
us children, she had to look after us you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you attend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 How many times would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well sometimes I would go - three times and sometimes I would stay in with my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you go to Sunday School or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Always went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. We used to have outings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were there any - what other social activities organized by the chapel did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 
Oh used to have - plays you know, little plays and - and what you call - cantatas they used to call them in those days you know. In fact my father used to compose the - the little pieces for them you know. Yes. I can remember I wasn't very big you know a
nd I was taking part in this little concert and I had a doll like this (she rocks her arms here to show me). And rocking it, the doll like this and sing a pretty song "oh my doll, my little maid. She is such a little darling. I'll nurse her all the day. Y
es. And that is what I was doing. Oh used to have - yes, used to have - yes, used to have lovely - little concerts and that in the chapel. Oh yes. We used to enjoy ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you belong to a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well there was not what you call a choir the
re. Only for - special occasions like an anniversary you see. And then they used to come up from Mount Pleasant from Mount Pleasant to help us. Of course my father really was the - the main one with the - men, because he had such fine - his good voice you
 see. A bass voice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 You mentioned the temperance club, the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes, Band of Hope. Quite a lot in the Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were you a member of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well we used to - sing and - recite and - and 
someone would talk of course, perhaps my father or - one of the other men you know a deacon perhaps would talk to them. And another thing we used to do too I seem to remember - we used to give a do you remember the big corn the chickens used to eat. Yes I
n
dian corn. Corn and they used to give us so many of those and we had to plant them in a pot, earth you know - and grow them. And the one that grew the best would have a point. I used to put mine in the cupboard under the stairs in the dark of course. And 
i
t used to be like that. Oh yes. Used to have lovely times in the Band of Hope. Yes. Have - Christmas parties, my father used to - give the give the cake and - and - and - every child had - oranges, perhaps two oranges I don't remember - one orange I think
 and a bag of sweets - when they left. That's Christmas time, every one in the Band of Hope, at Christmas time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were there any other things going on in the Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes, there was the Christian Endeavour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 What did they do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Well - 
more like - more like a proper service you know. All religious. And sometimes - someone would sing and - have a speaker and perhaps I would recite for I used to recite then you know and - and my father might recite I was quite small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 You did a lot of reciting did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Quite a lot, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did you have lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh he trained you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. yes. Yes, he trained us. and other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Oh yes. Always, my father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Were you told to say prayers at night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No, I don't remember family prayers, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10631877 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 No. No he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1924861 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13768631\charrsid810411 Do you know what his views were?
